# Calculator Unit Testing using NUnit

## Overview

This project demonstrates Unit Testing in .NET using the NUnit framework. The application contains a simple Calculator class with an Add() method. Automated test cases are written to validate the addition functionality.

## Objectives

* Understand Unit Testing concepts.
* Learn the difference between Unit Testing and Functional Testing.
* Implement automated tests using NUnit.
* Use TestFixture, SetUp, TearDown, and TestCase attributes.
* Verify expected results using Assert.That().
* Execute and manage tests through Visual Studio Test Explorer.

