## Calculator Implementation

The Calculator class contains an Add() method:

```csharp
public class Calculator
{
    public int Add(int a, int b)
    {
        return a + b;
    }
}
```

## Unit Test Implementation

The test project uses NUnit attributes:

* `[TestFixture]` – Defines the test class.
* `[SetUp]` – Runs before each test.
* `[TearDown]` – Runs after each test.
* `[TestCase]` – Provides parameterized test data.
* `Assert.That()` – Validates expected and actual results.

Example:

```csharp
[TestCase(10, 20, 30)]
[TestCase(5, 5, 10)]
[TestCase(1, 2, 3)]
public void Add_ShouldReturnExpectedResult(int a, int b, int expected)
{
    int actual = _calculator.Add(a, b);

    Assert.That(actual, Is.EqualTo(expected));
}
```

